Sentencas: The microstructure of the cermet support significantly influences the performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The properties required for the support include high electrical conductivity, necessary permeability, good match of thermal expansion with other layers, and high strength.
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, a flame-sprayed porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 cermet was designed as the support of SOFCs.
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effect of cermet microstructure on its gas permeability, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), and bending strength was investigated.
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Results show that the gas leakage rate of the cermet increased with the increase of polyester content in the starting powder.
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cermet exhibited a thermal expansion coefficient of 11.39 x 10(-6) K-1 from 25 to 1000 A degrees C. Moreover, the electrical conductivity of the cermet increased significantly and reached 1015 S/cm after sintering at 1000 A degrees C for 15 h. The bending strength of the cermet reached 171 MPa.
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cermet stability at high temperatures and SOFCs' performance are discussed.
Titulo: Microstructure and Properties of Porous Ni50Cr50-Al2O3 Cermet Support for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
